introduction this is an application by andrew williams, an australian building and construction inspector appointed under s 57 of the building and construction industry improvement act 2005 (cth) ("the bcii act"), for the imposition of penalties on the respondents, the construction, forestry, mining and energy union ("the union") and one of its organisers, robert mates, in respect of conduct alleged to be in contravention of ss 38 and 43 of the bcii act.
as alleged, the conduct was engaged in by mr mates at a construction site for the extension of a warehouse at 372 darebin road, alphington ("the site") on 28 and 31 july 2006.
